		},
		{
			"id": 1,
			"parent": 6,
			"text": "Staphylococcal enterotoxins ( SE ) stimulate T cells expressing the appropriate variable region beta chain of ( V beta ) T-cell receptors",
			"relation": "BACKGROUND",
			"tag": "Background"
		},
		{
			"id": 2,
			"parent": 1,
			"text": "and have been implicated in the pathogenesis of several autoimmune diseases . <S>",
			"relation": "ADDITION",
			"tag": "Background"
		},
		{
			"id": 3,
			"parent": 4,
			"text": "Depending on costimulatory signals ,",
			"relation": "CONDITION",
			"tag": "Background"
		},
		{
			"id": 4,
			"parent": 1,
			"text": "SE induce either proliferation or anergy in T cells . <S>",
			"relation": "ELABORATION",
			"tag": "Background"
		},
		{
			"id": 5,
			"parent": 4,
			"text": "In addition , SE can induce an interleukin-2 ( IL-2 ) nonresponsive state and apoptosis . <S>",
			"relation": "ADDITION",
			"tag": "Background"
		},
		{
			"id": 6,
			"parent": 0,
			"text": "Here , we show",
			"relation": "ROOT",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 7,
			"parent": 6,
			"text": "that SE induce dynamic changes in the expression of and signal transduction through the IL-2 receptor ( IL-2R ) beta and gamma chains ( IL-2R beta and IL-2R gamma ) in human antigen-specific CD4+ T-cell lines . <S>",
			"relation": "ATTRIBUTION",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 8,
			"parent": 6,
			"text": "Thus , after 4 hr of exposure to SEA and SEB , the expression of IL-2R beta was down-regulated ,",
			"relation": "ELABORATION",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 9,
			"parent": 8,
			"text": "IL-2R gamma was slightly up-regulated ,",
			"relation": "COMPARISON",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 10,
			"parent": 8,
			"text": "while IL-2R alpha remained largely unaffected . <S>",
			"relation": "COMPARISON",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 11,
			"parent": 8,
			"text": "The changes in the composition of IL-2Rs were accompanied by inhibition of IL-2-induced tyrosine phosphorylation of the Janus protein-tyrosine kinase 3 ( Jak3 ) and signal transducers and activators of transcription called Stat3 and Stat5 . <S>",
			"relation": "ADDITION",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 12,
			"parent": 8,
			"text": "In parallel experiments , IL-2-driven proliferation was inhibited significantly . <S>",
			"relation": "ADDITION",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 13,
			"parent": 8,
			"text": "After 16 hr of exposure to SE , the expression of IL-2R beta remained low ,",
			"relation": "ADDITION",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 14,
			"parent": 13,
			"text": "while that of IL2R alpha and IL2R gamma was further up-regulated ,",
			"relation": "COMPARISON",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 15,
			"parent": 13,
			"text": "and ligand-induced tyrosine phosphorylation of Jak3 and Stat proteins was partly normalized . <S>",
			"relation": "ADDITION",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 16,
			"parent": 13,
			"text": "Yet , IL-2-driven proliferation remained profoundly inhibited ,",
			"relation": "COMPARISON",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 17,
			"parent": 16,
			"text": "suggesting",
			"relation": "CAUSE-RESULT",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 18,
			"parent": 17,
			"text": "that signaling events other than Jak3/Stat activation had also been changed",
			"relation": "ATTRIBUTION",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 19,
			"parent": 18,
			"text": "following SE stimulation . <S>",
			"relation": "TEMPORAL",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 20,
			"parent": 6,
			"text": "In conclusion , our data suggest",
			"relation": "CONCLUSION",
			"tag": "Conclusion"
		},
		{
			"id": 21,
			"parent": 20,
			"text": "that SE can modulate IL-2R expression and signal transduction involving the Jak/Stat pathway in CD4+ T-cell lines . <S>",
			"relation": "ATTRIBUTION",
			"tag": "Conclusion"
		}
	]
}